<tr id="L417"><td><a href="#L417">417</a></td><td>ODO:  This trial was never about your husband, Mrs O'Brien. It was designed from the beginning to discredit the Federation, to show that the Maquis had their official sanction. Gul Evek's testimony made it clear that the situation had become untenable.</td></tr>

<tr id="L418"><td><a href="#L418">418</a></td><td>O'BRIEN:  Next they would have been demanding that the Federation colonies be disbanded.</td></tr>

<tr id="L419"><td><a href="#L419">419</a></td><td>SISKO:  Exactly. When Makbar saw Boone in the courtroom, she realised that we had the goods to embarrass the High Command in front of the entire populace.</td></tr>

